The schedule of classes is correct.  The class meets MF 1-3P in 606 Soda and W 1-3P in 330 Soda.

Classes for F16 begin on Wednesday, August 24th.  That means the first meeting of this class should be assumed to be on Wednesday, August 24 in 330 Soda.

children.subject:
Attendance for the first day is mandatory, but I'm not sure about Friday. However, Prof Garcia will give out codes for the class so don't worry about signing up for it during Phase 2 or the adjustment period, as it won't matter. 

However, know that you must have taken UCBUGG (the decal) before being eligible for this class.

For this class, if I have an unmovable obligation on the 26th and can't attend Friday's class, would this jeopardize my chances to get into the class? 

I really want to take this class, but if the absence on the 26th will prevent me from being in the class, I might have to re-think my unit distributions for Phase II.

Thanks!
